Package com.team254.lib.util.motion

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    HeadingProfileFollower
    Class to deal with angle wrapping for following a heading profile.
    MotionProfile
    A motion profile specifies a 1D time-parameterized trajectory.
    MotionProfileConstraints
    Constraints for constructing a MotionProfile.
    MotionProfileGenerator
    A MotionProfileGenerator generates minimum-time MotionProfiles to travel from a given MotionState to a given MotionProfileGoal while obeying a set of MotionProfileConstraints.
    MotionProfileGoal
    A MotionProfileGoal defines a desired position and maximum velocity (at this position), along with the behavior that should be used to determine if we are at the goal and what to do if it is infeasible to reach the goal within the desired velocity bounds.
    MotionSegment
    A MotionSegment is a movement from a start MotionState to an end MotionState with a constant acceleration.
    MotionState
    A MotionState is a completely specified state of 1D motion through time.
    MotionUtil  
    ProfileFollower
    A controller for tracking a profile generated to attain a MotionProfileGoal.
    SetpointGenerator
    A SetpointGenerate does just-in-time motion profile generation to supply a stream of setpoints that obey the given constraints to a controller.
    SetpointGenerator.Setpoint
    A Setpoint is just a MotionState and an additional flag indicating whether this is setpoint achieves the goal (useful for higher-level logic to know that it is now time to do something else).
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    MotionProfileGoal.CompletionBehavior
    A goal consists of a desired position and specified maximum velocity magnitude.
